Add support for Python 3.12

Handle DBus UnknownObject error when no collection is found (#43)

On Kubuntu 23.04, when trying to access a collection that doesn't
exist, it returns a UknownObject error instead of NoSuchObject.
Which makes me unable of installing the package on the system.

Handling this case, makes the KWallet dialog for creating the wallet
appear and the rest of workflow works as expected.

Co-authored-by: Dmitry Shachnev <mitya57@gmail.com>

Handle DBus UnknownObject error when no collection is found (#43)

On Kubuntu 23.04, when trying to access a collection that doesn't
exist, it returns a UknownObject error instead of NoSuchObject.
Which makes me unable of installing the package on the system.

Handling this case, makes the KWallet dialog for creating the wallet
appear and the rest of workflow works as expected.

Co-authored-by: Dmitry Shachnev <mitya57@gmail.com>

commit.message:
Add .readthedocs.yaml configuration file

See https://blog.readthedocs.com/migrate-configuration-v2/.
README.rst: Update Sphinx link to use https
pyproject.toml: Add Documentation and Issue Tracker URLs
Switch from setup.py/setup.cfg to pyproject.toml
Drop comment about Python 2 support
GitHub Actions: Add types-cryptography to fix mypy errors
Modernize type annotations
Drop support for Python < 3.9, add support for 3.11
GitHub Actions: Update to the latest versions of actions
Update documentation to reflect that we don't support asynchronous API
Releasing version 3.3.3
Bump copyright year
Remove useless inheritance from object
Fix code style issues
Run flake8 instead of pyflakes to check also code style

Collection.create_item: Handle case when service returns a prompt

Fixes #39.

Mention KWallet instead of KSecretsService

KSecretsService is dead, and KWallet got Secret Service support recently:
https://invent.kde.org/frameworks/kwallet/-/merge_requests/11
Add the previous commit to .git-blame-ignore-revs
Replace tabs with spaces in all Python files
Releasing version 3.3.2

Fix deprecation warning from jeepney 0.8.0+

jeepney has deprecated the use of unwrap=True in version 0.8.0 in
DBusConnection.send_and_get_reply().

The code code path affected by this flag is tiny and it was easy to
just move its intended behavior to the caller side of the
API.

Resolves issue #35.

Require Sphinx ≥ 3.0 for building docs on readthedocs

To make the class names in type annotations clickable.

See https://github.com/sphinx-doc/sphinx/issues/7341.
Add Python 3.10 to tested versions
SecretStorage ≥ 3.3 requires Python ≥ 3.6
Releasing version 3.3.1
Move from Travis CI to GitHub Actions
